nexml.meta:
Data for some features of the outgroup taxa have been compiled from: Chabanaud (1933), Amaoka (1969, 1972), Hensley (1977), Sakamoto (1984) and Cooper and Chapleau (1998b).
In the literature, a ninth species [of scophthalmid] is sometimes recognised: Scophthalmus maeoticus (Pallas, 1811) (Eschmeyer, 1998), but the available data do not permit us to consider this species as a valid taxon. [...]. For now, the most conservative approach is to consider these populations as conspecific, with the senior available name being Scophthalmus maximus.
Thus the four specimens of Scophthalmus maeoticus (MNHN 1999-248; MNHN 1999-58; MNHN 1999-291; MNSG 12717) are listed with the specimens of S. maximus. Arnoglossus thori (MNHN 1962-62) is listed in the Material and Methods but isn't in the matrix because its state characters are the same as those of Arnoglossus laterna.
For publication taxon Scophthalmus maximus: In the Catalog of fishes: synonym of "Psetta maxima". Bruno says "Scophthalmus maximus" is the valid name... MNSG synonym of MSNG?
